ic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":30,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William Snelling was born in 1425, in Hardwick, Bedfordshire, England, his father, John William Snelling, was 24 and his mother, Elizabeth Snelling, was 24. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Mrs- William Snelling. He died in 1509, in England, at the age of 84."},"et":{"1425–1509":"1425–1509","–Female":"Surnud","1450–1529":"1450–1529","1488–Female":"1488–Surnud","1401–1455":"1401–1455","1401–Female":"1401–Surnud","1425":"1425","1401":"1401","1455":"1455","1488":"1488","1450":"1450","1509":"1509","1529":"1529","Hardwick, Bedfordshire, England":"Hardwick, Bedfordshire, England","England":"England","Derby, Derbyshire, England":"Derby, Derbyshire, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"1425–1509":"1425–1509","–Female":"Kuollut","1450–1529":"1450–1529","1488–Female":"1488–Kuollut","1401–1455":"1401–1455","1401–Female":"1401–Kuollut","1425":"1425","1401":"1401","1455":"1455","1488":"1488","1450":"1450","1509":"1509","1529":